sql:
SELECT resource_component, category
FROM resource_components
ORDER BY LENGTH(resource_component) DESC;

SELECT resource_component, category
FROM resource_components
WHERE LENGTH(description) > 20;

SELECT treat_value
FROM study_data
WHERE study_data_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- 'Top-ranked studies' refers to the top 5 studies with the highest average treatment values for each resource component; 
- 'reducing erosion' refers to the category of the resource component being studied, which is filtered to 'erosion'; 
- 'better treatment outcomes' means that the average treatment value is greater than the average control value, indicating a positive effect of the treatment.

- "Long-term" refers to having more years post-treatment; 
- "Top three studies" refers to the studies with the highest years post-treatment for each location; 
- 'Plant Foliar Cover' is a data element in the study, which refers to the amount of plant cover on the foliage of plants.
